doc_summary_long: Longtime Sports Illustrated writer Frank Deford died on Sunday in Key West, Florida, according to the Washington Post. He was 78 years old. Deford started writing at Sports Illustrated in 1962 and had two lengthy stints with the magazine. The first came from 1962 to '89, when he became known as the master of the bonus story-the longest piece in each issue-and the second lasted from 1998 until his passing, during which time he continued to write his signature longform stories. He also worked with NPR's Morning Edition for 32 years. He retired earlier this month following his 1,656th NPR commentary.
